Tries to make a connection to the request port.

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the target host
port - tcp port to connect to

Responses\:
port opened - a successful connection was made
port closed - unable to make a connection
host not found - could not resolve hostname to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
addresses - list of addresses returned from DNS
aliases - list of aliases returned from DNS
addresspinged - actual IP address pinged

1013fb6b-df20-4558-a877-f85e358a1331.c3ae387f-a630-4259-af68-275cd54afc8e.prompt=The type of ports to be checked\: 1013fb6b-df20-4558-a877-f85e358a1331.d509148b-df2a-40ed-b954-8c25750f2de8.transition.description=The lowest port value (${lowestPort}) should be a non-negative integer. 1013fb6b-df20-4558-a877-f85e358a1331.dc69e9ce-4607-43e8-9f3f-f6b1b8f54c74.transition.description=The highest port value (${highestPort}) is greater than or equal to the lowest port value (${lowestPort}). 1013fb6b-df20-4558-a877-f85e358a1331.description=
Scan opened ports on give host  

Inputs\: 
 host - IP address Host name to be scanned
 lowestPort - lowest port range
 highestPort - highest port range
 portType - the type of ports to be scanned (TCP or UDP). If not specified, the TCP ports are scanned.

Note\:
 To scan specific port give same port as parameter for both Lowest Port and Highest Port, 

Responses\:
 success - the command was executed successfully
 failure - the command could not be executed

Result\:
 finalResult - Information about the ports' statuses on a given machine.

Extra results\:
 host - the IP of the host for which the ports are scanned
 ports - Number of ports scanned
 opened - Number of ports open
 closed - Number of ports closed
 dropped - Number of ports dropped
